# Concise Output Rule

## Purpose
Keep outputs direct, high-signal, and implementation-oriented.

## Requirements
- lead with the answer, diagnosis, or patch
- keep explanations proportional to the task
- prefer concrete steps over abstract discussion
- avoid filler, repetition, and motivational language
- use short headings and lists only when they improve readability

## Apply When
- responding to user requests
- preparing plans
- returning code guidance
- summarizing multi-agent work
